11. Quick Interview Explanation (Best Answer)

If an interviewer asks:

What is the 95th percentile?

Answer:

The 95th percentile means 95% of requests complete within a certain response time, and only 5% take longer. It helps identify slow requests that averages may hide and is widely used in performance SLAs.

12. Easy Way to Remember

Think of 100 users:

Percentile	Meaning
90th	90 users were faster
95th	95 users were faster
99th	99 users were faster

Only a small number experienced slow responses.

13. Golden Rule Used by Performance Engineers

Good system behavior:

Average < P90 < P95 < P99

But difference should not be too large.

Bad example:

Average = 1s
P95 = 6s
P99 = 15s

➡ Indicates serious latency spikes.

✅ Senior tester tip

Companies care about P95 and P99 more than average.

Because:

Users complain about slowest experience
not average experience.

